{
  "text": "The distribution of selected characteristics by tumor and by type of treatment is shown in Table 1 . BCS patients tended to be 2-3 years younger and tumor size tended to be smaller than TM patients. BCS patients who did not receive RT tended to be 1 year younger than BCS patients who received RT. The extent of node examination was comparable among the different subgroups. The number of nodes involved was particularly large in N+ patients who had TM and postsurgery RT (Table 1 ). Other details have been presented elsewhere [CITATION_1] .",
